ng\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"URL slug monitor\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=104813\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:517:\"<p>At All in One SEO, our mission is to make search engine optimization (SEO) easy for everyone, so more small businesses can grow and compete with the big guys. Today, I&#8217;m extremely excited to share our 3 newest features that&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-aioseo-4-2-3-faq-and-table-of-contents-blocks-all-new-url-slug-monitor/\">Introducing AIOSEO 4.2.3  FAQ and Table of Contents Blocks + All New URL Slug Monitor</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Benjamin Rojas\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11488:\"<p>At All in One SEO, our mission is to make search engine optimization (SEO) easy for everyone, so more small businesses can grow and compete with the big guys.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Today, I&#8217;m extremely excited to share our 3 newest features that will help you improve your website&#8217;s ranking:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>New <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-family); font-size: var(--font-size); color: initial;\">FAQ Block</span> + Schema Markup</li><li>Table of Contents Block</li><li>URL Slug Monitor</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>These are all designed to give you an edge as you implement SEO best practices on your WordPress site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s quickly look at how you can utilize these new features.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Improve SEO Click Through Rate with FAQ Block</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the new features we&#8217;re so excited to roll out with AIOSEO 4.2.3 is our FAQ block. This is a powerful tool that allows you to quickly and easily add Frequently Asked Questions to your posts or pages.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the biggest benefits of the FAQ block is that it automatically outputs your FAQs as JSON schema. This helps search engines understand what that particular page is about. As a result, you get a rich snippet on search engine results pages (SERPs) like the example below:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"474\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-serps.png\" alt=\"FAQs help you get rich results on search engine results pages. \" class=\"wp-image-105091\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-serps.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-serps-300x203.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-serps-600x406.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, the search result with FAQ block is twice as large as the other ones. This helps you get a higher clickthrough rate (CTR), stand out amongst your competitors, and it also increases the chances of getting the featured snippet. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>To add an FAQ block with proper schema markup, you simply need to click the <strong>Add Block</strong> button in the WordPress block editor, and then select the <strong>AIOSEO &#8211; FAQ</strong> block.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"420\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-1.png\" alt=\"The FAQ block will help you easily create an FAQ block on your posts and pages.\" class=\"wp-image-104816\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-1-300x180.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-1-600x360.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>After that, you can simply add Frequently Asked Questions related to your content or web page, so you can maximize your search traffic.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO FAQ block also comes with design options that let you customize the block&#8217;s background, text color, font size, and heading styles. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"406\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-options.png\" alt=\"You can customize the FAQ block any way you want.\" class=\"wp-image-105254\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-options.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-options-300x174.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-options-600x348.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>What makes our FAQ block better than others in the industry is that we separate the FAQ Schema markup (JSON+LD) from the actual FAQ content output. This means that you can actually hide the FAQ blocks from the front-end while still getting the rich snippets. You won&#8217;t find this feature in any other WordPress SEO plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This use-case is particularly helpful if you want to have more control over the design &amp; layout of how FAQs are displayed. Often time site owners already have FAQs listed in their webpage, and they simply want proper Schema markup output, and we have made that easy for you.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With all these customizations options, now you can offer the best user experience while maximize your SEO rankings with a rich snippet and higher click through rate.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>WordPress Table of Contents Block that You Will Love</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There are dozens of table of content block plugins available for WordPress, but they all have one problem. While they automatically generate the table of content, none of them let you customize the headings or give you the option to selectively hide specific items.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Wouldn&#8217;t it be nice if there was a solution that not only saved you time, but also gave you the flexibility you need to improve your editorial workflow?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This was the exact problem our team was having, so we built the solution into AIOSEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"395\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1.png\" alt=\"The Table of Content blocks helps you automatically create a table of contents on your posts. \" class=\"wp-image-104817\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1-300x169.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1-600x339.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;re proud to introduce the most powerful Table of Content (ToC) block for WordPress. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Our AIOSEO Table of Contents (ToC) block automatically generates the table of content from the headings in your post to help you save time. But you can also:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Customize the Heading text</li><li>Choose to hide and re-order headings inside the block</li><li>and even customize the anchors</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The Table of Contents block also has many SEO benefits because it not only helps offer the best user experience, but it can also enhance your Google search results with helpful jump links.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"294\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps.png\" alt=\"Adding a table of contents can enhance your Google search results with jump links.\" class=\"wp-image-105094\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps-300x126.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps-600x252.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Jump links are an excellent way to encourage visitors to click on your website, and go straight to the section they&#8217;re most interested in. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Like everything else AIOSEO, adding the Table of Contents block is super easy. Simply click on the Add block button and choose the Table of Contents block.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"369\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/adding-table-of-contents.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-105260\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/adding-table-of-contents.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/adding-table-of-contents-300x158.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/adding-table-of-contents-600x316.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Avoid 404 Errors with the URL Slug Monitor</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Last but not least, were very excited to announce our URL Slug Monitor. This automatically checks to see if any of your page URLs have changed. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If the slug monitor detects a URL change, then it will prompt you to add a redirect, so you can avoid 404 errors and continue to rank high.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"338\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/url-slug-monitor-new.png\" alt=\"The URL slug monitor helps eliminate 404 errors when editing permalinks.\" class=\"wp-image-105047\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/url-slug-monitor-new.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/url-slug-monitor-new-300x145.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/url-slug-monitor-new-600x290.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Clicking on the <strong>Add Redirect to Improve SEO</strong> button will take you to the <strong>Redirection Manager</strong> where you can properly implement a 301 redirect.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"329\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/add-redirects-slug-monitor.png\" alt=\"Implementing redirects is easy with the URL Slug Monitor.\" class=\"wp-image-104815\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/add-redirects-slug-monitor.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/add-redirects-slug-monitor-300x141.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/add-redirects-slug-monitor-600x282.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>To make your life easy, our URL slug Monitor automatically fills out the source URL and target URL, so you can properly add the redirect without any errors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is an important feature that helps you easily maintain your permalinks when any URLs are changed as it eliminates the risk of creating 404 errors on your site. This ensures your visitors have a good experience on your site. It also helps you keep all the SEO gains intact.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides these 3 new features, weve made several notable improvements to many of the features you already love. You can see those in our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/changelog/\" title=\"full product changelog\">full product changelog</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>What are you waiting for? Update your site to AIOSEO 4.2.3 to unlock these new powerful features.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if youre not yet using AIOSEO, make sure to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">install and activate the plugin today</a>, so you can outrank your competitors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have any questions about any of these features, please leave a comment below or reach out to our customer support team. We&#8217;re always ready to help.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Our commitment to making AIOSEO, the easiest and best WordPress SEO plugin is only getting stronger as we continue to win together with our customers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;re so grateful for your continued support, feedback, and suggestions. Please keep those suggestions and feature requests coming.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope you enjoy using these new SEO features as much as we enjoyed creating it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>&#8211; Benjamin Rojas</em></p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-aioseo-4-2-3-faq-and-table-of-contents-blocks-all-new-url-slug-monitor/\">Introducing AIOSEO 4.2.3  FAQ and Table of Contents Blocks + All New URL Slug Monitor</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:107:\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-aioseo-4-2-3-faq-and-table-of-contents-blocks-all-new-url-slug-monitor/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2:\"11\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n									